a:5:{s:5:"title";s:50:"OpenCRM introduces Timeline in the Assets module";s:16:"text-format-info";a:3:{s:10:"text-final";s:640:"<p>OpenCRM expanded its Timeline feature to cover the Assets module.</p>
<p>What’s new</p>
<p>The Timeline is now available within the Assets area, providing a chronological view of activity/history related to asset records.</p>
<p>Why it matters</p>
<p>Assets often require ongoing tracking (updates, changes, related activity). A Timeline view makes it easier to review context quickly by showing events in time order without jumping between sections.</p>
<p>Additional note</p>
<p>OpenCRM also references an overview of the Assets feature for organizations that are not currently using OpenCRM for asset tracking.</p>
